-- Deutsche Bahn, Train Drivers Union Agree to Negotiation Terms
-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 2012-01-05T18:35:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-05/deutsche-bahn-train-drivers-union-agree-to-negotiation-terms.html
Deutsche Bahn AG (DBHN)  and the GDL German
train drivers union have agreed to a timetable for negotiations
for a future labor agreement, the union said in an e-mailed
statement.  Negotiations will take place on Feb. 8 in Berlin, the union
said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 